                                                                       Top
   Special Notices:

   The Bureau of Labor Statistics is able to produce the occupational
   employment and wage estimates displayed on this website because of the
   timely co-operation of employers throughout the United States. If your
   workplace received an Occupational Employment Statistics survey form
   please complete it and return it to the State employment security
   agency that sent it to you. If you have returned a completed survey
   form, Thank you!

   Old OES and New SOC occupational classification systems: Begining with
   the 1999 estimates the OES program discontinued the use of five-digit
   OES codes to identify occupational categories and began using the
   Standard Occupational Classification system.
