   Related Links:
     * Standard Occupational Classification-- The SOC system is used by
       government agencies to classify workers into occupational
       categories for the purpose of collecting, calculating, or
       disseminating data.
     * National Compensation Survey-- 450 occupations - occupations are
       classified according to 1990 Occupational Classification System
       Manual; data include information on the level of difficulty and
       complexity of work.
     * Employment Projections-- employment trends by industry and
       occupation



